SIMPLE: blown
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blown
<hw>Blown</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Swollen; inflated; distended; puffed up, as cattle when gorged with
green food which develops gas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Stale; worthless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Out of breath; tired; exhausted.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Their
horses much blown.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Covered with the eggs and larv⟦ae⟧ of flies; fly
blown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blown</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Blown
<hw>Blown</hw>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <def>Opened; in blossom or having
blossomed, as a flower.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blow-off</ent>⟦br⟧
